After analyzing the dataset containing information about movies, several interesting findings emerged. Firstly, when examining the average rating of each genre, it becomes apparent that certain genres tend to receive higher ratings on average compared to others. For instance, dramas and thrillers often garner higher ratings, reflecting their popularity among audiences for their compelling storytelling and suspenseful plots. On the other hand, genres like horror and comedy exhibit more variability in their ratings, indicating a wider range of audience preferences within these categories. Additionally, the analysis reveals that some genres have distinct subgenres, as evidenced by the exploration of subgenres under the main genre "Action." This finding highlights the diverse and nuanced landscape of film genres, showcasing how certain genres can encompass a broad spectrum of themes and styles. Overall, these insights shed light on the dynamics of audience preferences and the rich tapestry of genres within the realm of cinema.
